<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Curtain" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Curtain,</orth> subst. a cloth hanging to shut out the light or conceal something: <emph>the --s being close</emph> (of the bed) <bibl n="shak. luc 367" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 367</bibl>. <cit><quote>spread thy close c., love-performing night,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 3.2.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 2, 5</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>wherefore have these gifts a c. before 'em?</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 1.3.134" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 3, 134</bibl></cit>. <emph>To draw the c.</emph> or <emph>--s</emph> == a) to close it: <bibl n="shak. mv 2.7.78" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 7, 78</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 2.9.84" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 9, 84</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 5.3.59" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 3, 59</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 5.3.59" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 3, 59</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wt 5.3.59" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 3, 59</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.3.32" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 3, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 5.2.34" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 V, 2, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.6.90" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 6, 90</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 5.2.104" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. V, 2, 104</bibl>. b) to open it: <bibl n="shak. luc 374" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 374</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 2.7.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 7, 1</bibl> <cit><quote>(draw aside).</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 2.9.1" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 9, 1</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.251" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 251</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.1.73" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A IV, 1, 73</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.1.72" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 1, 72</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 3.2.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 2, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.1.142" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 1, 142</bibl>. -- Used for the eyelids: <cit><quote>the fringed --s of thine eye advance,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.408" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 408</bibl></cit>. For ensigns: <cit><quote>their ragged --s poorly are let loose,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.2.41" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 2, 41</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>